# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# Signatory database files
*.db
*.db-journal
*.db-wal
*.db-shm

# Local working notes
design/NEXT.md

# Working-pair shared log — kaizen entries, deferred refactors,
# held-over problems. Useful locally; intentionally not tracked.
sync/

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/
.DS_Store
.claude/settings.local.json
CLAUDE.md

# Filestore — analysis output, clones, and ingested data.
# This directory is project-local working state, not source.
# Its location is configurable via --filestore-dir and
# signatory.config.toml; .gitignore covers the default.
filestore/

# Per-user signatory state (DB, certs, logs, pidfile).
# Normally lives at ~/.signatory/ and is out of the repo, but a
# misconfigured --cert-dir, accidental `signatory init`, or a
# symlinked home could land it here. Ignoring proactively keeps
# private key material (certs/*.key), cert bundles, and DB
# contents from ever entering git.
.signatory/

# Built binaries at the repo root.
# Anchored with leading slash so each pattern matches ONLY the root-level
# binary, not the cmd/<name>/ source directory (which previously got
# silently swallowed by the bare `signatory` pattern, hiding new files
# in that directory from `git status` and `git add`).
/signatory
/smoke-mcp
/dogfood-metrics-bin
/dogfood-metrics-smoke

# Dogfood telemetry runtime data (per design/agent-otel.md).
# The receiver writes OTLP-JSON here; the report generator writes
# per-session reports here. Both are local-only working state, not
# source. The dogfood-metrics/README.md and any committed config
# files at the directory root are NOT ignored.
dogfood-metrics/raw/
dogfood-metrics/sessions/

# Migration-time backup snapshots produced by store.OpenSQLite when
# running migrations on an existing DB. Tests / generators that open
# the store may create these; they're not source-of-truth.
*.db.backup-*
